This paper discusses program specialisation in functional and logic programming, which are subfields of programming languages (cs.PL) and automated reasoning (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the challenge of designing automatic control for correctness, efficiency, and termination, which are issues relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the Burstall-Darlington unfold/fold transformation framework, which is a technique used in program analysis and optimization (cs.SC).
